'''Maghnes Akliouche''' (born 25 February 2002) is a French professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for {{French football updater|Monaco}} club [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].<ref name="SW">{{Soccerway|id=maghnes-akliouche/664215|access-date=15 September 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
Akliouche made his professional debut for [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] on 16 October 2021, coming on as a substitute in a 2–0 loss away against [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]].<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Maltret|first1=Laurent|last2=Federici|first2=Thomas|date=16 October 2021|title=Résultat et résumé OL - Monaco, Ligue 1 Uber Eats, 10e journée|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-1/2021-2022/ol-monaco-live/515572|access-date=16 October 2021|newspaper=L'Équipe|language=fr}}</ref> On 7 January 2023, he scored his first senior goal against [[Rodez AF]] during the [[2022–23 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/french-coupe-de-france-monaco-vs-rodez-aveyron-jan-07-2023-game-boxscore-111368 |title=Monaco 2–2 Rodez Aveyron |publisher=FOX Sports |date=7 January 2023 }}</ref> Later that year, on 13 August, he netted his first [[Ligue 1]] goal in a 4–2 away win over [[Clermont Foot 63|Clermont]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/scoring-4-goals-as-monaco-makes-it-a-success-in-clermont/ |title=Scoring 4 goals, AS Monaco make it a success in Clermont! |publisher=AS Monaco FC |date=13 August 2023 }}</ref>

On 19 September 2024, Akliouche made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut, scoring a goal in a 2–1 win over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/de/news/maghnes-akliouche-is-your-mvp-against-barcelona-after-scoring-the-first-goal-40060978 |title=Maghnes Akliouche is your MVP against Barcelona after scoring the first goal |publisher=OneFootball |date=20 September 2024 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Akliouche holds both French and Algerian nationalities.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sid |date=19 December 2022 |title=Le binational Maghnes Akliouche fait du chantage à Belmadi |url=https://fennecfootball.com/la-jeune-pepite-franco-algerienne-maghnes-akliouche-fait-du-chantage-a-belmadi/ |access-date=7 January 2024 |website=Fennec Football |language=fr}}</ref> He was a member of the [[France Olympic football team|France Olympic]] squad that won the silver medal on home soil in [[2024 Summer Olympics|2024]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/akliouche-and-magassa-final-squad-olympics/ |title=Akliouche and Magassa are in the final squad for the Olympics! |publisher=AS Monaco FC |date=8 July 2024 }}</ref>

He received his first call-up to the [[France national football team|France senior team]] in August 2025, ahead of their [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group D|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] and [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Entwistle |first=Luke |title=Maghnes Akliouche celebrates France call-up with more goals for Monaco |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/sep/01/maghnes-akliouche-france-call-up-goals-monaco-strasbourg |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=2 September 2025 |date=1 September 2025}}</ref> On 5 September 2025, he made his first senior international appearance, coming off the bench against Ukraine in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Dorian|last=Bonzom|title=Equipe de France Maghnes Akliouche entré en jeu, la France démarre bien sa campagne de qualifs face à l'Ukraine (analyse et notes)|url=https://madeinmonegasque.ouest-france.fr/infos/article-qualifs-cdm-2026-les-notes-des-bleus-face-a-l-ukraine-la-france-demarre-bien-sa-campagne-mais-perd-doue-et-dembele-sur-blessure-494410.html|newspaper=[[Ouest-France]]|date=5 September 2025|access-date=15 September 2025}}</ref> Later that year, on 16 November, he scored his first international goal in a 3–1 away win over [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] during the same World Cup qualification.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2025/didier-deschamps-on-maghnes-akliouche-hes-moved-up-a-notch/ |title=Didier Deschamps on Maghnes Akliouche: 'He's moved up a notch.' |publisher=Get Football News France |date=17 November 2025 }}</ref>

